# mstack project memory

## Read first

Before **meaningful** UI, UX, branding, or product-copy work, **skim** the project’s memory file (this repo: **`docs/PROJECT_MEMORY.md`**). If your app uses another path, document it in `AGENTS.md`.

Rules **do not** auto-save every conversation. Persistence happens when someone **edits this file**—usually after the user agrees to a durable preference.

## When to update

Add a **dated bullet** under the right section when the user **explicitly** confirms something long-lived, for example:

- “Always use …” / “Never ship …”
- Brand voice, density, motion level
- Canonical product names or glossary choices

Keep entries **short**. Do not dump full chat transcripts.

## Conflicts

- **Technical decisions** → `templates/ADR_TEMPLATE.md` or `docs/DECISIONS.md` (this repo).
- **Exploration only** → no update until the user locks it.

## Pairing

- `mstack-design-research.mdc` for external references (web only with user permission).
- `mstack-docs-devx.mdc` when memory belongs in contributor-facing docs too.
- `mstack-session-handoff.mdc` — in a new chat, user can `@` or paste **`docs/PROJECT_MEMORY.md`**.

## Hygiene

Respect `mstack-permissions.mdc` and `mstack-token-discipline.mdc`—small, intentional edits only.
